Hi, Anmol -

It&#39;s not clear to me what the issue is -- what do you want to happen 
that isn&#39;t?

Heritrix can accept cookies, or not, based on the FetchHTTP 
&#39;ignore-cookies&#39; setting. The HTML extractor should find URIs in a META 
REFRESH tag and consider them &#39;R&#39; hops; the question is whether the URI 
is new (in this case it is) and whether your scope would accept the 
discovered URI for subsequent crawling.

- Gordon @ IA

